  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training Ugandans in Trauma Informed Care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project equips local leaders in Uganda with mental health and trauma informed care knowledge and skills, so they can support survivors in their communities, disrupt cycles of trauma and violence, and break the stigma around mental health.  Trainings are designed for everyday community leaders who may have little to no prior mental health knowledge - including teachers, health workers, faith leaders, local government leaders, and more.</narrative>
  </description>
